## Neutral Gray Environment

One final detail completes the viewing environment:
the page uses a **neutral gray background** with zero chroma.
This prevents any hue bias from affecting color perception —
unlike warm beige or cool blue-grays, true neutral gray doesn't push reds, greens, or blues in any direction.
Combined with the off-white Polaroid borders,
this creates a consistent viewing context that works equally well in light and dark modes.
The result is closer to a color-neutral print viewing environment
than the stark white or deep black backgrounds common on photo sites.

