This doesn't reduce the number of trapped or unused cells —
that's inherent to the cell-span approach —
but it does reduce wasted space *within* the cells that photos occupy.
The effect is modest, and borders shift the aspect ratio of all photos (even those already at target),
but since perfectly matched photos are in the minority,
the net effect is still an improvement in space utilization.

