## Adding Visual Playfulness: Rotation

One more detail softens the mechanical feel: **slight random rotation**.
We rotate each photo by a small random angle drawn from a normal distribution.
The result: Polaroid cards that look scattered by hand rather than aligned by machine.

<!-- TODO: Add cell-span-tilted.svg diagram showing rotation effect -->

The rotation is subtle — just enough to break rigid alignment without creating chaos.
Combined with the inconsistent gap alignment inherent in the cell-span layout,
this produces a layout that feels organic and tactile,
more like prints pinned to a wall than tiles in a spreadsheet.

